### MediSync Backend Registration API Tests

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000/api

### 1. Doctor Registration
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "testdoc@example.com",
  "password": "Password123!",
  "fullName": "Dr. Test Doctor",
  "licenseNo": "SLMC-TEST001",
  "specialization": "General Physician"
}

###

### 2. Patient Registration
POST {{baseUrl}}/patient/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "nic": "123456789V",
  "password": "Password123!",
  "fullName": "Test Patient",
  "dateOfBirth": "1995-05-15",
  "gender": "Male",
  "district": "Colombo",
  "contactInfo": "0770000000"
}

###

### 3. Pharmacy Registration
POST {{baseUrl}}/pharmacy/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Test Pharmacy",
  "district": "Kandy",
  "address": "123 Main St, Kandy",
  "regNo": "PH-TEST-001",
  "adminEmail": "admin@testpharmacy.com",
  "adminPassword": "Password123!",
  "adminName": "Test Pharmacist"
}

###

### 4. Hospital Registration
POST {{baseUrl}}/hospital/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Test Hospital",
  "type": "private",
  "district": "Galle",
  "address": "456 Hospital Rd, Galle",
  "regNo": "HOSP-TEST-001",
  "email": "admin@testhospital.com",
  "password": "Password123!"
}

###

### 5. Admin Login (Needed to get token for Admin Registration)
# Run 'npm run seed:users' first to create this Super Admin
POST {{baseUrl}}/admin/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "superadmin@medisync.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

###

### 6. Admin Registration (Requires Bearer Token from previous step)
@adminToken = your_token_here

POST {{baseUrl}}/admin/register
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

{
  "fullName": "New Sub Admin",
  "email": "subadmin@medisync.com",
  "password": "Password123!"
}
